Subject: =?UTF-8?q?fix(slayzone):=20extensions=20modal=20=E2=80=94=20keep?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20shell=20focused=20+=20hide=20inlay=20from=20window=20manager?=
 =?UTF-8?q?s?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

With the extensions modal (inlay) open, the inlay stole key focus from the shell
and external window managers (Magnet etc.) resized the inlay instead of the main
window. Two fixes:

- The host shows the inlay with ShowInactive (not Show) so the SHELL keeps key
  focus — window managers act on the main window with no "click the background
  first" dance. The user clicks into the inlay's web content to type (Web Store
  search / 1Password).
- BrowserNativeWidgetMac hides the inlay NSWindow from the Accessibility API
  (setAccessibilityElement:NO), so window managers skip it even if it does gain
  focus (they resize the AX focused window, bypassing the `movable`/non-resizable
  flags). Trade-off: VoiceOver can't navigate the inlay's web content as a
  separate window.
---
 .../browser/slayzone/slayzone_embedded_tab_host.cc   | 12 ++++++++++--
 .../ui/views/frame/browser_native_widget_mac.mm      |  5 +++++
 2 files changed, 15 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/chrome/browser/slayzone/slayzone_embedded_tab_host.cc b/chrome/browser/slayzone/slayzone_embedded_tab_host.cc
index 9f12f355d47a2..c901f20b6af2f 100644
--- a/chrome/browser/slayzone/slayzone_embedded_tab_host.cc
+++ b/chrome/browser/slayzone/slayzone_embedded_tab_host.cc
@@ -368,7 +368,11 @@ void SlayzoneEmbeddedTabHost::OpenExtensionsWindowOnProfile(
         }
       }
       PositionExtensionsInlay(body);
-      extensions_browser_->window()->Show();
+      // ShowInactive (not Show): the inlay must NOT steal key focus from the shell —
+  // the shell stays the focused window so window managers (Magnet) act on it,
+  // and there's no "click the background first" dance. The user clicks into the
+  // inlay's web content when they want to type (search / 1Password).
+  extensions_browser_->window()->ShowInactive();
       return;
     }
     // A different identity was requested — tear the old window down first.
@@ -424,7 +428,11 @@ void SlayzoneEmbeddedTabHost::OpenExtensionsWindowOnProfile(
       w->SetBounds(BodyToScreen(body));
     }
   }
-  extensions_browser_->window()->Show();
+  // ShowInactive (not Show): the inlay must NOT steal key focus from the shell —
+  // the shell stays the focused window so window managers (Magnet) act on it,
+  // and there's no "click the background first" dance. The user clicks into the
+  // inlay's web content when they want to type (search / 1Password).
+  extensions_browser_->window()->ShowInactive();
   LOG(INFO) << "[embedded_tab] opened extensions inlay browser="
             << extensions_browser_.get();
 }
diff --git a/chrome/browser/ui/views/frame/browser_native_widget_mac.mm b/chrome/browser/ui/views/frame/browser_native_widget_mac.mm
index c1a891273501d..3984fbdbf93b2 100644
--- a/chrome/browser/ui/views/frame/browser_native_widget_mac.mm
+++ b/chrome/browser/ui/views/frame/browser_native_widget_mac.mm
@@ -539,6 +539,11 @@ NativeWidgetMacNSWindow* BrowserNativeWidgetMac::CreateNSWindow(
     // programmatically via Widget::SetBounds (movable only gates user drags).
     ns_window.movable = NO;
     ns_window.movableByWindowBackground = NO;
+    // Hide the inlay from the Accessibility API so external window managers
+    // (Magnet etc., which resize the AX focused window and bypass `movable`)
+    // skip it and act on the shell window instead. Trade-off: VoiceOver can't
+    // navigate the inlay's web content as a separate window.
+    [ns_window setAccessibilityElement:NO];
   }
 
   return ns_window;
